The paper deals with resource allocation in a multiple access channel (MAC) with and without security constraints. It uses game theoretic learning to propose algorithms for power allocation and maximizing the weighted sum-utility of users. It also considers the scenario where users can cooperate to avoid unfair policies. These topics are closely related to information theory (cs.IT), game theory (cs.GT), cryptography (cs.CR), networking (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
